args: N-not a chance! We'll hold out until...
Sorry! Sorry! I'm here! Right then.\nHave at thee and...so forth.
Let's go! Plenty of me to go around...
*sigh* What a mess. Still, looks like\nwe pushed 'em back for the moment.
Oh, for the love of... This is too much.
Meanwhile, at the south side\nof the Svenitlan base...
Heh heh. Nice! I should be able to\nsneak in while they're distracted.
Right then! Looks like the attacks\nare finally starting to let up.
Everyone, come quickly!\nThe storehouse is on fire!
Hurry! Put it out before we\nlose all of our supplies!
Fire in the storehouse destroyed\nmore than half our rations.
Then the assault from the north was a\nmere diversion? Hmm. Impressive.
I'm sorry, Commander.\nI should have been more vigilant.
How long do you intend to run?
If you had ordered the troops to maintain\na proper lookout, the saboteur would\nhave been spotted sooner.
I won't speak ill of those who stand\ncourageous in the face of adversity,\neven if they fail.

But I will ALSO not tolerate failure that
stems from the refusal of a soldier to
face their own flaws. Such are cravens,
and I have no use for cravens.
If you make the same mistake again,\nthe punishment will be swift and severe.\nAm I understood?
And you there! In the corner!\nShow yourself.
Wait, we've had a tunnel this whole time?\nWho even MADE it?
Uh, I don't know? But an engineer told\nme about it some time ago. She, uh, said\nit was an escape tunnel.
But it's all narrow and...um...crumbly.\nSo no one uses it.
Is it safe to say that very few people\nknow about this tunnel?
If you used it to get here, that must mean\nit comes out beyond the enemy's camp.
Which means WE can use it to\nescape this deathtrap.
Negative. Everyone is to remain here\nand await reinforcements.
Right. Of course. Silly me...\nWell then, what brings you to our\nlittle slice of heaven, Noelle?
...So higher-ups were captured on their\nway back from negotiating an armistice\nwith Barthe and are in need of rescue?
It would seem there is a faction within\nBarthe that finds the truce unfavorable.
Probably the same faction that's breathing\ndown our damn necks right now.
What would your move be, Joachim?\nWould you attempt to rescue the captives,\nor leave them to fend for themselves?

Normally, I'd be more than happy to rescue
some big shots and bask in the glory,
but we've barely got the forces to hold
this base as it is.
I hate to say it—especially since a lot\nof this is my fault—but I think we need\nto leave 'em to their own devices.
Agreed. A rescue attempt is simply\ntoo great a risk at this time.
Having said that, if we DID succeed in this\nrescue, it may be possible to preserve\nthe truce and avoid further bloodshed.
Now is the time for justice.\n...Joachim!
I'm assigning a squad to your command.\nDo what must be done.
Sorry, did you say a SQUAD?

I have no one else I can trust with this
assignment. Rest assured that I will
oversee the defense of this base in
your absence, however.
You can do this, Joachim.\nI have faith in you.
Ma'am! I am to command a squad and\nrescue individuals crucial to our cause!
Er, um, if you need to know\nwhere everyone is, I can...guide you?
